<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E233FFCB73C7FBE90481FBB4" bold="true" box="[422,503,1030,1051]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A Male holotype habitus, retrolateral view; B Female paratype, habitus, retrolateral view; C Male, frontal view; D Female, frontal view; E Male, left chelicera, retrolateral view; F Male, left leg I, retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B 0.15 mm; C, 0.08 mm; D, 0.06 mm; E, 0.02 mm; F, 0.40 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="B9C005C1E233FFCB72A6FB6F07B8FB12" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F165564AE233FFCB72A6FB6F07B8FB12" blockId="3.[199,962,1152,1213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E233FFCB72A6FB6F0416FB36" bold="true" box="[199,352,1152,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Distribution.</emphasis>
At present known only from the 
<typeStatus id="2E61E8E8E233FFCB70B4FB6E0673FB36" box="[725,773,1153,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="69E14ACFE233FFCB710EFB6F06C2FB36" box="[879,948,1152,1177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1373,1395]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,577,1330]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1423,558,1349]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map showing the currently known localities of Shearella spp. ● Shearella alii sp. nov. Shearella lilawati Lehtinen, 1981 ▲ Shearella sanya Lin &amp; Li, 2010 ♦ Shearella selvarani Lehtinen, 1981." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="C3AE8A58E233FFCB72A6FB4B0446FB12" bold="true" box="[199,304,1188,1213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Remark.</emphasis>
First record of the genus from 
<collectingCountry id="89CD16DAE233FFCB70ECFB4B07BCFB12" box="[653,714,1188,1213]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
